<font color="#FF0000">WAR IS NOT A GAME</font><br>
<tt>Tue Sep 16 23:52:36 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Art,<br><br>
I for one know exactly why.  I have a son working there now.  A civilian.  You mess with the pack, you get your ass kicked pure and simple (not verbally).  They studied your darkest fears and that is exactly what they did.  Intell notes captured said to not engage the ROCs at any cost.  Charlie trembled when they were on patrol.  They killed everything.  I wouldn't begin to tell stories on this site.  They knew what it took to win.  Get into your enemies mind and stay there.  Humane wars always get more people killed on both sides.<br><br>
I saw a soldier stand motionless stripped in the monsoon rains for 24 hours in front the COs hooch just for not eating what the CO wanted.  That was a gift, some were shot.<br><br>
We shackle our warriors by the norms of the non warring.  Men die for this reason.  But I am to presume they die well, while some pompous ass stands by and passes judgement on his tactics.  What do you tell a bullet or a SAM, be fair, be gentle, you know the rules.  No!!  Use the enemies tactics and fight on his ground only better.<br><br>
That's what a ROC was.
